1
00:01:42,280 --> 00:01:43,050
Tong,

2
00:01:43,280 --> 00:01:44,690
hurry up, the car will be here soon.

3
00:01:46,430 --> 00:01:47,380
Are you ready, Tong?

4
00:01:50,040 --> 00:01:50,820
Tong!

5
00:01:53,640 --> 00:01:54,540
What's wrong, Tong?

6
00:01:55,120 --> 00:01:56,980
Sis, I'm cold.

7
00:02:01,950 --> 00:02:02,540
You're burning again.

8
00:02:02,560 --> 00:02:04,820
I've already turned it up to the max, but it's not helping.

9
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:13,820
Mr. Xia has booked a hotel for us.

10
00:02:13,840 --> 00:02:15,100
The conditions there are better.

11
00:02:15,310 --> 00:02:16,450
Once we get there, everything will be fine.

12
00:02:30,280 --> 00:02:31,980
Back in 2008, I knew

13
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:33,380
we'd make it sooner or later.

14
00:02:35,430 --> 00:02:36,890
We've gone around in circles,

15
00:02:37,840 --> 00:02:39,100
but we're still together.

16
00:02:40,870 --> 00:02:41,850
Today, when Yan Dan told me,

17
00:02:41,870 --> 00:02:43,260
I thought to myself,

18
00:02:43,590 --> 00:02:44,610
could it be you?

19
00:02:45,470 --> 00:02:46,380
And sure enough, it is.

20
00:02:46,400 --> 00:02:47,980
See, we're so fated!

21
00:02:49,520 --> 00:02:50,380
I only believed in fate

22
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:51,890
when I was a kid.

23
00:02:51,910 --> 00:02:53,130
Now that I'm older, I've grown out of that.

24
00:02:53,960 --> 00:02:55,690
The medical aesthetics world is small, after all.

25
00:02:56,120 --> 00:02:57,850
What goes around comes around, it's inevitable.

26
00:02:59,150 --> 00:03:00,570
Are you still mad?

27
00:03:01,240 --> 00:03:02,570
I left Gemu

28
00:03:03,120 --> 00:03:05,100
because Tang hurt my feelings,

29
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:06,130
not because of you.

30
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:07,780
I don't think

31
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:09,290
there's any personal grudge between us.

32
00:03:09,560 --> 00:03:10,500
I completely agree.

33
00:03:12,150 --> 00:03:13,500
Since you're lacking

34
00:03:13,520 --> 00:03:15,220
a bit of medical knowledge,

35
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:17,130
let me remind you.

36
00:03:17,520 --> 00:03:19,610
Yan Tong's condition is pretty serious, you know?

37
00:03:20,630 --> 00:03:21,730
Are you serious?

38
00:03:21,910 --> 00:03:23,220
I even had Mr. Du take a look,

39
00:03:23,240 --> 00:03:24,220
and he treated it.

40
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:26,260
He said it'll take about a week to recover.

41
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:28,660
It's not as bad as you're making it sound.

42
00:03:29,910 --> 00:03:31,340
Du Jun hasn't checked back in, huh?

43
00:03:31,520 --> 00:03:32,170
Don't tell me about it.

44
00:03:33,520 --> 00:03:34,450
This weekend,

45
00:03:34,710 --> 00:03:36,290
during surgery, his heart started acting up,

46
00:03:36,310 --> 00:03:37,170
and he fell.

47
00:03:37,190 --> 00:03:38,260
He's still in the hospital now.Alright,

48
00:03:39,280 --> 00:03:40,410
let's not talk about him.

49
00:03:40,840 --> 00:03:41,570
What about you?

50
00:03:41,870 --> 00:03:42,890
Are you really here

51
00:03:43,360 --> 00:03:45,380
for those two kids?

52
00:03:46,030 --> 00:03:47,170
This doesn't seem like you.

53
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:48,730
Are you here for Gemu?

54
00:03:53,030 --> 00:03:53,610
Alright.

55
00:03:54,080 --> 00:03:56,100
Since you've noticed the two kids,

56
00:03:56,470 --> 00:03:57,570
it's their lucky day.

57
00:03:58,280 --> 00:03:59,980
Let me thank you for them.

58
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:01,410
Starting today,

59
00:04:01,470 --> 00:04:03,170
I'm officially handing them over to you.

60
00:04:05,190 --> 00:04:06,660
If their condition is as serious as you say,

61
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:08,380
as a doctor, you can't just stand by and do nothing, right?

62
00:04:10,680 --> 00:04:12,060
What's with Gemu and Jiao Ai?

63
00:04:12,080 --> 00:04:13,980
There shouldn't be any barriers, right?

64
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:17,050
In the end, we're all here for the patients.

65
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:19,580
Li Qi,

66
00:04:19,920 --> 00:04:21,170
I've known you for a long time.

67
00:04:21,360 --> 00:04:23,730
But seriously, you've got to stop talking

68
00:04:23,950 --> 00:04:25,050
in riddles like that.

69
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:26,780
Your aesthetics training center's

70
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:28,250
been open for a while now.

71
00:04:28,480 --> 00:04:29,460
And honestly, I don't believe Yan Dan and Yan Tong

72
00:04:29,480 --> 00:04:30,810
are your only victims.

73
00:04:31,390 --> 00:04:33,050
It's only a matter of time before the whole thing blows up in your face.

74
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:34,780
You think I came here today

75
00:04:35,120 --> 00:04:36,460
to make a deal with you?

76
00:04:38,630 --> 00:04:39,660
That look on your face,

77
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:41,410
same as back then.

78
00:04:49,190 --> 00:04:50,140
Once you step out that door,

79
00:04:50,560 --> 00:04:51,730
we're strangers.

80
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:54,140
I'll take this loss as a lesson learned.

81
00:04:55,040 --> 00:04:55,930
I'll admit I lost.

82
00:04:57,630 --> 00:04:58,580
But I'm not giving up.

83
00:04:59,480 --> 00:05:00,410
We'll see how things play out.

84
00:05:02,430 --> 00:05:03,220
Fine.

85
00:05:04,920 --> 00:05:06,730
You don't wanna go to the police?

86
00:05:07,870 --> 00:05:08,700
I will.

87
00:05:12,120 --> 00:05:12,900
Zhou Jingwen!

88
00:05:15,390 --> 00:05:16,780
If you wanna go down with me, that's fine.

89
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:18,170
I've got nothing to lose.

90
00:05:19,310 --> 00:05:20,100
Unlike you.

91
00:05:20,360 --> 00:05:22,290
You fought tooth and nail for seven or eight years to become a doctor.

92
00:05:22,310 --> 00:05:23,540
If this scandal gets out,

93
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:25,170
all of that's gone, just like that.

94
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:27,460
What else can you even do

95
00:05:27,720 --> 00:05:28,850
if you're not a doctor?

96
00:05:34,190 --> 00:05:35,170
100K isn't much.

97
00:05:35,310 --> 00:05:36,980
But it's enough to start fresh somewhere else.

98
00:05:39,830 --> 00:05:40,850
Think about it.

99
00:06:12,270 --> 00:06:14,250
You're doing pretty well for yourself now.

100
00:06:14,920 --> 00:06:15,980
Looking at where you are today, I honestly feel

101
00:06:16,870 --> 00:06:18,250
that 100 grand I gave you back then

102
00:06:18,680 --> 00:06:21,340
is the best investment I ever made in my life.

103
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:27,340
Since that's your attitude,

104
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:28,900
you don't need to worry about

105
00:06:28,920 --> 00:06:30,100
Yan Dan and Yan Tong anymore.

106
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:33,780
What's done is done.

107
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:34,730
I accept the consequences.

108
00:06:35,750 --> 00:06:36,930
But the fact that you're acting like you're untouchable,

109
00:06:36,950 --> 00:06:38,540
talking to those girls like that,

110
00:06:38,830 --> 00:06:40,340
because from the begining,

111
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:41,540
you're under a fake identity.

112
00:06:42,390 --> 00:06:44,660
Even if they wanted to report you, they couldn't.

113
00:06:45,600 --> 00:06:47,930
Because no one can trace anything back to a "Xia Ling,"

114
00:06:47,950 --> 00:06:48,610
right?

115
00:06:51,720 --> 00:06:53,490
Well, I have the call recordings between you and Yan Dan.

116
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:03,140
Alright then.

117
00:07:06,680 --> 00:07:07,370
One more thing.

118
00:07:07,390 --> 00:07:08,980
I want your opinion on something.

119
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:12,810
If Jiao Ai and Gemu merged,

120
00:07:13,720 --> 00:07:15,020
what should the new name be?

121
00:07:16,040 --> 00:07:17,900
Jiaoge? Jiaomu?

122
00:07:18,430 --> 00:07:20,850
Or maybe Aige, Aimu?

123
00:07:22,630 --> 00:07:23,610
You didn't know?

124
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:25,100
Just this morning,

125
00:07:26,070 --> 00:07:28,340
Tang already confirmed the acquisition intent.

126
00:07:32,240 --> 00:07:33,140
You

127
00:07:33,160 --> 00:07:35,340
really shouldn't keep dwelling on

128
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:37,020
that little unpleasantness between us back in the day.

129
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:39,340
The equity transfer

130
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:40,810
is happening in the next couple of days anyway.

131
00:07:40,950 --> 00:07:42,580
So think about it, what really

132
00:07:42,750 --> 00:07:43,780
matters most right now?

133
00:08:00,830 --> 00:08:02,370
Damn, I'm too late.

134
00:08:23,430 --> 00:08:23,980
Hello?

135
00:08:24,390 --> 00:08:25,730
Why weren't you answering my calls?

136
00:08:25,750 --> 00:08:27,490
Did you see the messages I sent?

137
00:08:27,680 --> 00:08:29,660
It's Li Qi. She's the one behind Yan Dan, Yan Tong,

138
00:08:29,680 --> 00:08:31,220
and that training scam.

139
00:08:32,750 --> 00:08:33,530
I know.

140
00:08:33,750 --> 00:08:35,130
I just saw her.

141
00:08:36,510 --> 00:08:37,460
She told me to stay out of it,

142
00:08:37,480 --> 00:08:38,700
not to get involved with those two girls.

143
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:39,850
Wait, what?

144
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:41,250
And what did you say?

145
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:44,250
Say something!

146
00:08:45,030 --> 00:08:46,730
You do realize Li Qi already moved Yan Dan and Yan Tong

147
00:08:46,750 --> 00:08:48,340
somewhere else, right?

148
00:08:49,790 --> 00:08:52,060
Look, I don't have the energy to explain everything right now.

149
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:53,940
What's that supposed to mean?

150
00:08:54,630 --> 00:08:55,420
Wait,

151
00:08:56,150 --> 00:08:57,370
is this whole thing really that complicated?

152
00:09:01,080 --> 00:09:02,700
Don't tell me you actually agreed to her terms.

153
00:09:03,750 --> 00:09:05,490
All for Gemu?

154
00:09:06,030 --> 00:09:06,940
We'll talk about this later.

155
00:09:27,960 --> 00:09:29,850
You know what? Playing on a real court

156
00:09:29,870 --> 00:09:31,340
is actually kinda fun.

157
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:33,010
Totally different from practicing at home.

158
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:34,130
Look at that day.

159
00:09:34,480 --> 00:09:35,610
It was so good.

160
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:39,490
Where's Tang? Why isn't he here yet?

161
00:09:39,750 --> 00:09:41,700
He said his dad just woke up this morning.

162
00:09:41,720 --> 00:09:43,610
He's trying to make it over as soon as he can.

163
00:09:44,440 --> 00:09:46,610
I'll call him, he has to come.

164
00:09:47,080 --> 00:09:48,220
What's going on?

165
00:09:49,030 --> 00:09:49,980
Come, this way, please.

166
00:09:52,390 --> 00:09:52,890
Ms. Shi.

167
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:53,820
Ms. Shi.

168
00:09:54,390 --> 00:09:55,130
Mr. Qin.

169
00:09:55,150 --> 00:09:56,220
Welcome.

170
00:09:57,630 --> 00:09:58,530
Remember her?

171
00:09:58,670 --> 00:10:00,130
Same year as Qiao Yang.

172
00:10:00,150 --> 00:10:01,730
Also one of Gemu's founders.

173
00:10:01,750 --> 00:10:02,820
Zhou Jingwen.

174
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:03,370
Of course

175
00:10:03,390 --> 00:10:04,250
I remember!

176
00:10:04,270 --> 00:10:05,220
Hi, Shi Jin.

177
00:10:05,240 --> 00:10:06,820
You were a legend at our school.

178
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:08,730
Still stunning as ever.

179
00:10:10,150 --> 00:10:11,770
This must be Mr. Dong, right?

180
00:10:12,720 --> 00:10:15,580
You're a huge name in my WeChat feed.

181
00:10:15,750 --> 00:10:17,010
A few of my friends

182
00:10:17,030 --> 00:10:18,650
are your regular clients.

183
00:10:18,870 --> 00:10:20,300
You've made them

184
00:10:20,320 --> 00:10:22,010
all age-defying beauties.

185
00:10:23,550 --> 00:10:24,980
They even gave me a nickname,

186
00:10:25,150 --> 00:10:26,370
"The Ladies' Friend."

187
00:10:26,910 --> 00:10:28,010
Feel free to drop by any time!

188
00:10:30,030 --> 00:10:32,100
Mr. Chu, Ms. Shi, shall we take our seats?

189
00:10:32,120 --> 00:10:34,010
Please.

190
00:10:34,120 --> 00:10:35,130
Come, Mr. Chu.

191
00:10:35,440 --> 00:10:37,130
Let me offer you a toast.

192
00:10:37,960 --> 00:10:39,890
For the past half year, I haven't had time for anything else,

193
00:10:39,910 --> 00:10:41,460
just been dealing with hospital stuff.

194
00:10:41,750 --> 00:10:43,940
You helped me resolve a huge burden.

195
00:10:43,960 --> 00:10:45,420
I'll drink this whole glass.

196
00:10:48,390 --> 00:10:49,300
Times have changed.

197
00:10:49,320 --> 00:10:50,770
Now it's these young folks

198
00:10:50,790 --> 00:10:51,770
who are dragging an old man like me along.

199
00:10:53,270 --> 00:10:55,770
I often see your interviews, news features,

200
00:10:56,200 --> 00:10:57,700
pop up on my phone.

201
00:10:57,910 --> 00:10:59,460
It makes me so proud.

202
00:10:59,870 --> 00:11:01,770
Every time I see one, I share it.

203
00:11:01,790 --> 00:11:03,460
Every time I see one, it goes on my Moments.

204
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:05,460
Having such an outstanding student,

205
00:11:05,480 --> 00:11:06,420
as a teacher,

206
00:11:06,440 --> 00:11:08,220
how can I not show off a little?

207
00:11:09,150 --> 00:11:11,770
That's just your information bubble talking.

208
00:11:12,030 --> 00:11:13,730
You keep getting my updates

209
00:11:13,750 --> 00:11:15,610
not because I'm so great,

210
00:11:15,630 --> 00:11:17,770
but because you follow me,

211
00:11:17,790 --> 00:11:20,530
so the algorithm keeps pushing my stuff to you.

212
00:11:20,550 --> 00:11:22,010
Well, I have to follow you. Definitely!

213
00:11:23,240 --> 00:11:23,850
Sir,

214
00:11:24,080 --> 00:11:25,820
to be honest,

215
00:11:26,240 --> 00:11:28,530
ever since I decided to invest in the hospital sector,

216
00:11:28,550 --> 00:11:31,130
we've looked at, what, nearly a hundred hospitals?

217
00:11:31,150 --> 00:11:31,890
More than that, actually.

218
00:11:31,910 --> 00:11:32,580
Right?

219
00:11:33,720 --> 00:11:34,940
These organizations,

220
00:11:34,960 --> 00:11:36,610
on the surface,

221
00:11:36,630 --> 00:11:39,010
they all look like fireworks and roses.

222
00:11:39,030 --> 00:11:41,580
Beautiful numbers, flashy data.

223
00:11:41,790 --> 00:11:43,010
But behind the scenes,

224
00:11:43,030 --> 00:11:46,890
the lack of proper management is beyond imagination.

225
00:11:47,120 --> 00:11:50,490
There was this one hospital we checked out in South China.

226
00:11:50,510 --> 00:11:50,890
Right?

227
00:11:50,910 --> 00:11:51,530
Yes.

228
00:11:51,630 --> 00:11:53,610
Our talks were going well,

229
00:11:53,910 --> 00:11:55,890
but when we reviewed the documentation,

230
00:11:55,910 --> 00:11:59,420
we found a medical dispute on record.

231
00:11:59,790 --> 00:12:03,060
They operated on a patient

232
00:12:03,320 --> 00:12:04,820
without getting consent from the family.

233
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:05,850
So what happened?

234
00:12:06,120 --> 00:12:08,700
The family just wouldn't let it go.

235
00:12:08,720 --> 00:12:10,940
Didn't matter how successful the surgery was.

236
00:12:10,960 --> 00:12:12,650
There was no peace after that.

237
00:12:13,240 --> 00:12:15,580
What does that tell you?

238
00:12:16,030 --> 00:12:18,010
Lack of standardized procedures.

239
00:12:18,360 --> 00:12:19,010
Exactly.

240
00:12:19,030 --> 00:12:20,220
Right?

241
00:12:20,240 --> 00:12:21,100
Yeah.

242
00:12:21,120 --> 00:12:21,610
That's right.

243
00:12:21,630 --> 00:12:23,730
Did you end up signing with that hospital?

244
00:12:23,750 --> 00:12:24,490
We did.

245
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:30,420
If I had signed back then, we wouldn't even be having this meeting now.

246
00:12:32,150 --> 00:12:32,940
Exactly.

247
00:12:32,960 --> 00:12:35,460
A single overlooked dispute

248
00:12:35,480 --> 00:12:36,580
can be a symptom

249
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:39,340
of countless lapses in standard procedures.

250
00:12:40,080 --> 00:12:41,980
Although performance is important,

251
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:45,420
what I value more is the philosophy behind the operation.

252
00:12:45,440 --> 00:12:45,820
Yes.

253
00:12:45,840 --> 00:12:48,580
If our values and mindset don't align,

254
00:12:48,600 --> 00:12:50,490
then even if we're friends,

255
00:12:50,510 --> 00:12:52,060
we shouldn't move forward together, am I right?

256
00:12:52,080 --> 00:12:52,730
Absolutely.

257
00:12:52,750 --> 00:12:54,650
I completely agree with your philosophy.

258
00:12:54,750 --> 00:12:57,060
Standardized medical practice must come first.

259
00:12:57,360 --> 00:12:59,340
Ensuring patients' safety,

260
00:12:59,360 --> 00:13:01,370
and constantly improving the quality of our service

261
00:13:01,440 --> 00:13:03,530
has always been Gemu's goal.

262
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:05,420
And now with Mr. Chu backing us,

263
00:13:05,440 --> 00:13:07,340
you can truly rest easy.

264
00:13:07,670 --> 00:13:09,250
Since you put it that way,

265
00:13:09,270 --> 00:13:11,820
I'd better do a thorough evaluation of Gemu.

266
00:13:12,360 --> 00:13:13,060
No problem at all.

267
00:13:13,080 --> 00:13:14,010
You're welcome anytime!

268
00:13:14,030 --> 00:13:15,100
Absolutely, you're always welcome!

269
00:13:15,120 --> 00:13:16,340
Come on, everyone,

270
00:13:16,510 --> 00:13:17,130
come.

271
00:13:17,150 --> 00:13:17,850
Apologies,

272
00:13:17,870 --> 00:13:18,370
everyone, sorry I'm late.

273
00:13:18,390 --> 00:13:19,100
Sorry.

274
00:13:19,120 --> 00:13:20,490
Mr. Tang, what took you so long? Let me introduce you.

275
00:13:20,510 --> 00:13:22,650
This is Mr. Tang, our investor at Gemu.

276
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:24,010
Shi Jin.

277
00:13:24,670 --> 00:13:25,650
Hello everyone!

278
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:26,940
Pleasure to meet you, Ms. Shi.

279
00:13:27,150 --> 00:13:28,060
Take a seat.

280
00:13:28,150 --> 00:13:28,940
Jingwen,

281
00:13:28,960 --> 00:13:30,650
that location you sent me wasn't accurate.

282
00:13:30,960 --> 00:13:32,130
